#RenalFailure  #Anemia: Loss of erythropoietin leads to normochromic, normocytic anemia
#RenalFailure #Hypocalcemia: Wthout 1,25 dihydroxy form of vitamin D, the body will not absorb enough calcium from the gut
#RenalFailure #Osteodystrophy: Low calcium levels leads to secondary #hyperparathyroidism.
#RenalFailure #Bleeding: Platelets do not work normally in a uremic environment
#RenalFailure  Infection: The same defect occurs with #neutrophils
#RenalFailure #Pruritus: Unclear reasoning; urea accumulating in skin causes itching

It's disheartening to see how many people are coming down with #RenalFailure
Studies have shown that roughly 1 in 5 Nigerians have some form of chronic kidney disease which can ultimately lead to #RenalFailure
Kidney Replacement Therapy is needed when the level of kidney function has dropped below 10-15% of its original capacity #RenalFailure
Renal (Kidney) Replacement Therapy can be undergone through either #Dialysis or #KidneyTransplant - these are current options #RenalFailure
About 100 new cases per million population every year are diagnosed with #RenalFailure
That translates to - at the very least - roughly 15,000 new cases every single year. #RenalFailure
Raw figures have conservatively put the number of both new + old cases to be about 300 per million population #RenalFailure
In an unrevised population of 150 million, that comes to about 45,000 persons who require dialysis or transplant at anytime! #RenalFailure
The damning fact is only about 1000 people have access to a form of #RenalReplacementTherapy; which in this case is Dialysis #RenalFailure
The costs of dialysis treatments are prohibitive and unreasonable #RenalFailure
Between #5.2 & #10 million would be the average cost of managing a patient with #RenalFailure that required dialysis.
It is glaringly obvious that this malady would gouge holes even in the deepest of pockets! The option? Government Intervention #RenalFailure
The National Health Insurance Scheme in Nigeria provides between 3 to 6 dialysis sessions for people covered in the scheme. #RenalFailure
What happens after that person has been diagnosed with established #RenalFailure? How does such a person pay for his/her ongoing treatments?
Even those who qualify for a transplant will need dialysis pending their definitive treatment. There are also other issues. #RenalFailure
The best way to combat this menace is by awareness, prevention, screening programs and incorporating healthy lifestyles #RenalFailure
Dialysis costs need to be driven down! The NHIS needs to pick up the slack for the costs for patients with #RenalFailure
